<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><template xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns="openEHR/v1/Template" xmlns:uuid="java:java.util.UUID"><id>72bb35a2-809d-4467-8aa7-1f9efecc3679</id><name>Diagnostic Imaging - Interventional Radiography - IR Caecostomy Percutaneous  Order</name><description><lifecycle_state>Initial</lifecycle_state><details><purpose>For ordering a(n) IR Caecostomy Percutaneous </purpose><use/><misuse/></details><other_details><item><key>MetaDataSet:Sample Set </key><value>Template metadata sample set </value></item><item><key>Acknowledgements</key><value/></item><item><key>Business Process Level</key><value/></item><item><key>Care setting</key><value/></item><item><key>Client group</key><value/></item><item><key>Clinical Record Element</key><value/></item><item><key>Copyright</key><value/></item><item><key>Issues</key><value/></item><item><key>Owner</key><value/></item><item><key>Sign off</key><value/></item><item><key>Speciality</key><value/></item><item><key>User roles</key><value/></item></other_details></description><annotations path="[openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1]"><items><item><key>Imaging.Body Part</key><value>%=AB</value></item><item><key>Imaging.Post Procedure Instructions</key><value>Bedrest: Bedrest post procedure to be determined by the Radiologist.;Vitals: q15 minutes x 4 hours, q30 minutes x 2 hours, q1 hour x 4 hours, site assessment with vital signs checks.;Leave dressing insitu, change if soiled. Assess for hematoma/bleeding at puncture site.;Notify Radiologist if patient related concerns arise.;Resume previous infusion orders as indicated on chart or Normal Saline lock IV. Discontinue peripheral IV prior to discharge.;Antibiotics and any other post procedural medications as per orders.;Nutrition: Clear fluids progressing to diet as tolerated when bowel sounds present or passage of flatus/feces. Continue with high fiber diet as per orders.;Ambulate post procedure as tolerated as per orders.;Outpatient Post Procedure Care: Admit to patient care unit post procedure. Discharge 2 days post procedure if no problems. Family will be contacted with date and time of appointment to have the C-tube exchanged, usually 6 weeks after initial insertion. Send the patient home with dressings, tape, polysporin, 2 feeding bags, EMLA cream and silicone Foley catheters. Send patient home with the "First week post Discharge orders" and the "After First week discharge orders." Teaching should include recovery from anesthetic or sedation, pain control, procedure related symptoms, activity restrictions, dressing care and post-procedural complications. Flush catheter twice daily with 10 mls saline. Continue pre-procedural enema routine for 9 days post procedure after which antegrade enemas begin. Unusual symptoms including fever, difficulty breathing or skin reactions immediately to your doctor and seek immediate emerency care if required. Report bleeding or hematoma, apply direct digital pressure and seek immediate emergency care. Report any sign of redness or increased pain to your doctor. Report if cramping, nausea or vomiting occurs, call to discuss change of protocol. Report if you notice the tube is pulled back, has leakage around the site or increased pain to the Radiology department. If the tube falls out, put 8 Fr Foley in hole (do not blow up balloon) and call IR department.</value></item><item><key>Imaging.Laterality</key><value>No</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Clinical Decision Support Requirements</key><value>Diagnostic Imaging to provide guidelines to support the lab and medication requirements for interventional radiography procedures.</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Contraindications</key><value>Contrast Allergies: If there is a chance of an allergy to Contrast media, notify Diagnostic Imaging.</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Patient Requirements</key><value>Laboratory: Serum Creatinine and GFR, PT PTT/INR Group, CBC required upon admission.;Medications: As per orders, maintenance IV as per weight. 3.3% Dextrose and 0.3% NaCl infusion with 20 mmol KCL/L 500 mL IV continuous access peripheral line. Continue medications as usual with sip of water, excluding medications as directed by ordering provider (anticoagulants or diabetic medications).If the patient is on any blood thinning medications including Apixaban (Eliquis), Aspirin (ASA), Coumadin (Warfarin), Dabigatran (Pradax), Heparin (Enoxaparin, Dalteparin, Fragmin etc.) Plavix (Clopidogrel) or Rivaroxaban (Xarelto) consult with the ordering provider for instructions on holding medications. Consult with Diagnostic Imaging as required. Diabetic patients may require further instructions taking medications on the morning of the procedure, as per ordering physician.  Blood glucose check upon admission. ;IV requirements: Initiation of a peripheral intravenous is required. (Edmonton Zone) Connect to 3.3% Dextrose and 0.3% NaCl infusion with 20 mmol KCL/L 500 mL IV as per orders as per Maintenance IV.;Nutrition: (Edmonton Zone) Clear fluids 2 days prior to procedure. Nothing to eat or drink from midnight the day before the procedure.;Vitals: Baseline vitals required prior to DI procedure.;Imaging: (Edmonton Zone) Obtain supine xray of abdomen on admission to assess bowel status, as more bowel preparation may be required prior to procedure. </value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Clinical Communication</key><value>Inpatient Clinical Communication: Patient in hospital attire with undergarments removed, intact hospital and applicable allergy ID bands. Personal needs of patient (e.g. use of washroom) must be attended to prior to leaving the ward. Consent is required. If the patient is unable to give consent independently, ensure that the co-decision maker or alternate decision maker(s) who have Power of Attorney, along with a legal consent form, accompany the patient to Diagnostic Imaging.  Send reading glasses/hearing aids. Notify department if a translator is required. Complete patient chart, including current medication record and vital signs record, must accompany patient to the Diagnostic Imaging department.;Outpatient Clinical Communication: Signed consent will be required at the time of appointment. If the patient is unable to give consent independently, ensure that the co-decision maker or alternate decision maker(s) who have Power of Attorney, accompany the patient to Diagnostic Imaging. Bring reading glasses, hearing aids or a translator if required. Please follow the nutrition requirements: No solid foods 6 hours prior to procedure and continue clear fluids 3 hours prior to procedure. Continue medications with a sip of water. If you are on any blood thinning/anticoagulant medications please discuss with your doctor for instructions on holding. You will be admitted to the hospital post procedure.</value></item></items></annotations><definition xsi:type="INSTRUCTION" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1" concept_name="Service request" max="1" name="IR Caecostomy Percutaneous "/><integrity_checks xsi:type="ArchetypeIntegrity" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1"><digest id="MD5-CAM-1.0.1">B48161A11EF4549FFAE82EE73B385AF5</digest></integrity_checks><integrity_checks xsi:type="ArchetypeIntegrity" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.service_request_information.v1"><digest id="MD5-CAM-1.0.1">230A8D964017E1FD7AC82EBDEE0202A6</digest></integrity_checks></template>